    "Even within the same dialect, pronunciation can vary significantly across different regions, including differences in phonemes, tones, and rhythm (Gong et al. 2011).",
    "For example, the specific differences in the Uyghur dialects of the Hetian and Luobu regions are manifested in vowels (Sun (4) WER = S + D + I N.",
    "This increases the complexity of speech recognition systems and makes extracting speech features difficult.",
    "Furthermore, in multilingual environments, people often communicate employing a mix of several dialects or a hybrid language combining dialects with Mandarin (Yang and Hu 2021), presenting additional challenges for recognition models.",
